China opens up its capital markets, 
doubling the amount foreigners can invest in the country. U.S. 
auto sales jumped 13% in March. The U.S. Fed says there's no 
need for another round of quantitative easing.  Bloomberg's 
Susan Li reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 02:38
 